# Static Site Only (GitHub Pages)

This project must remain a static site deployable on GitHub Pages with no paid hosting requirements.

## Allowed

- Static assets and pages: HTML, CSS, client-side JavaScript, images, fonts, and static JSON/data files.
- Build-time only tooling that outputs static files (for local development or pre-deploy generation).
- GitHub Pages compatible deployment output.

## Not Allowed

- Any backend/server runtime code (Node servers, Express, APIs, Python/PHP/Ruby/Go servers, serverless functions).
- Databases or runtime data stores requiring hosted infrastructure.
- Features that require paid hosting services to function.
- Any architecture requiring a persistent process after deploy.

## Implementation Guidance

- Prefer client-side integrations with third-party services only when they work without running your own backend.
- If a requested feature needs a server, propose a static-friendly alternative first.
- Keep all changes compatible with direct static hosting on `github.io`.
